&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a Deliverability and Compliance Specialist to maintain Kit’s healthy reputation and provide hands-on support to help creators reach the inbox of their subscribers. You will support all Kit customers and our deliverability in a key role that reports directly to the Manager of Creator Growth and Deliverability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is great at both analyzing data to solve problems and teaching complex concepts. They also need to be an excellent communicator with customers, teammates, and industry contacts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role looks like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing quick and high-quality support for all deliverability support tickets and escalations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring all accounts to ensure compliance and providing support to customers when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping build Kit’s reputation in the deliverability space by creating educational content, among other strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training members of the general support team on key deliverability concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating documentation and blog posts to support customers with deliverability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with account approvals to provide excellent support while maintaining Kit’s reputation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing deliverability audits for high-value accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Blocklist monitoring and remediation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spam trap monitoring and outreach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remediation of any delivery issues by communicating with mailbox providers and other industry contacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active participation and representation at M3AAWG meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with product and engineering to improve features and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The right candidate should have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of customer support experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of deliverability support experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with the email deliverability landscape (mailbox providers, blocklists, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of email authentication (SPF, DKIM, DMARC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of spam traps, list health, sender reputation, and email compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and relationship-building skills – with an ability to communicate complex information internally and externally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A creator-focused mindset - extremely motivated to help creators succeed by providing excellent customer service and education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A desire to be a company representative by producing content, partnering with industry connections, and attending deliverability events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a 100% remote environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend our bi-annual retreats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have enthusiasm and belief in our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://convertkit.com/mission&quot;&gt;mission, vision, and values&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
